content:
Install the Service Data Kit

First, install the Service Data Kit.
IMPORTANT If you already have the Service data kit installed, upgrade or reinstall it to ensure that itâ€™s up to date and contains the Knowledge bundle and Einstein Conversation Mining bundle. Upgrading the data kit is necessary to access the latest enhancements to Service Intelligence.

In Data Cloud, click the gear icon and then select Data Cloud Setup.
Under Configuration, select Salesforce CRM.
Find the Service Cloud bundle, and click the menu button on the right. Select Install.
To upgrade the Service data kit, navigate to the Service Cloud bundle, click the menu button on the right, and select Upgrade.

To view the data kit details, go to Data Cloud Setup. Under Tools, select Data Kits and then click ServiceDK.
title: Installing the Service Data Kit for Salesforce
